This was so yummy. My boyfriend who claims that he doesn't like sweet potatoes devoured it. I did make a few changes/addtions. I used all sweet potatoes. I simmered the cream and sage mixture to infuse the cream and shorten the cooking time a bit. I caramelized some onions and layered them and some pecorino cheese with the sweet potato. Then topped the whole thing off with fresh bread crumbs more pecorino and these delicious fried shallots that we get from the asian market. I'm sure this recipe is awesome as written but I couldn't resist guilding the lily a bit. ;-)

