I made this as a side for Thanksgiving dinner and the flavors went perfectly with the dressing and turkey. Based on the suggestions from the other reviewers, I cut the cream to 3/4 cup and substituted milk for the other 3/4 cup. This made it a bit runny, but we didn't have the heaviness/greasiness that others complained about. I supplemented the gruyere with some parmesan as well. Will make again!

